13th Avenue, east side, north from W. 28th Street, showing fenced areas above and below 29th Street. The latter is to be developed into a truck loading station for the Erie Railroad. The John T. Stanley structure is at the S. E. corner of 30th Street; a point where this thoroughfare changes its identity to 12th Avenue. The elevated West Side Highway will make a bend there as shown in the later view.

View 1: March 17, 1929
View 2: April 22, 1931
View 3: August 24, 1940

P. L. Sperr

12th Avenue, east side, from W. 30th (right) to 33rd (left) Streets, showing the New York Central Railroad yards. In the center are the sheds that lie between 31st and 32nd Streets. The 2-story hay lofts on the left are on the north side of 33rd Street. In the background is the outstanding Empire State Building.
